SSV Review Requirements
Overview
The SSV (Site Survey) review is a pre-processing step that runs before the existing LU reconciliation workflow. It operates at the address level, and every address in scope must receive exactly one final action as output.
This workflow will be implemented in FME. The requirements below are written for code generation purposes.

Input Data
SourceDescriptionBuild List (BL)Existing list of addresses with type (MDU/SDU), bus_number, LU count, DMP Building KeySSV tableSite survey results, already validated. Contains unit count and existence status per addressBelmap polygon layerPolygon layer with polygon ID mappable to building key. Used for spatial context

Data Model Assumptions

Each address has: dmp_building_key, address_id, bus_number (nullable), type (MDU/SDU), lu_count
Each SSV record has: address_id (or equivalent join key), ssv_unit_count, ssv_status (existing / not_existing / empty)
Belmap polygon layer has: polygon_id (maps to dmp_building_key), geometry
A Building Group (BG) is a grouping of MDU/SDU entities — not all MDUs belong to a BG, and a BG with only 1 entity is acceptable


Polygon Linkage
Every address must be linked to a Belmap polygon using the following priority:

Primary: match polygon_id to dmp_building_key
Fallback: spatial match — point-in-polygon lookup using address location against Belmap geometry

An address that cannot be linked via either method is a data quality issue and should be flagged separately (outside the main action logic).

Final Action Values
Every address must receive exactly one final action:
ActionDescriptionKeepNo change neededAddNet new address from SSV, not present in BL, polygon check passedRemoveSSV status = not_existing or emptyModifyType conversion (SDU↔MDU) or LU count adjustment requiredReviewRequires human intervention — routed to a separate team

Business Rules
1. MDU with 1 LU in BL
Trigger: address type = MDU AND lu_count = 1

Join to SSV on address
If ssv_unit_count = 1 → action = Modify, convert to SDU, set bus_number to NULL
If ssv_unit_count > 1 → action = Modify, keep as MDU, target lu_count = ssv_unit_count (LUs to be added using existing bus_number sequence logic)


2. SDU in BL but SSV indicates MDU
Trigger: address type = SDU AND ssv_unit_count > 1

action = Modify, convert to MDU
Original SDU address retains its existing bus_number (NULL or otherwise)
Add new LUs to reach ssv_unit_count, using existing bus_number sequence suggestion logic


3. Address in BL, SSV = not existing or empty
Trigger: address exists in BL AND (ssv_status = not_existing OR ssv_status is empty/null)

action = Remove
Flagged for removal — goes through normal removal process, not automatic deletion


4. Address in SSV but not in BL (net new)
Trigger: address exists in SSV but has no match in BL

Perform polygon linkage (see Polygon Linkage section)
Check if other addresses exist in the same polygon

If other addresses exist in same polygon → action = Review, route to separate team
If no other addresses in polygon → action = Add




5. No change needed
Trigger: address exists in BL, SSV confirms existing status, no type or count mismatch

action = Keep


Output Specification
One row per address. Minimum output fields:
FieldDescriptionaddress_idAddress identifierdmp_building_keyBuilding keybus_numberCurrent or updated bus_numbertypeCurrent or updated type (MDU/SDU)lu_count_blLU count from BLlu_count_ssvLU count from SSVfinal_actionOne of: Keep, Add, Remove, Modify, Reviewaction_reasonShort description of why the action was assignedpolygon_idMatched Belmap polygon IDpolygon_match_methodid_match or spatial_match

Scope & Exclusions

SSV data is already validated — treat all SSV records as authoritative, no re-validation needed
Building Group entity count (1 entity in a BG) is not a trigger — acceptable by design
Edge case: MDU present in BL but absent from SSV entirely — out of scope for now, to be defined later
This workflow produces the input state for the LU reconciliation step, which runs after


Notes for FME Implementation

SSV table can be read as a standard FME table reader
Polygon linkage: use PolygonOverlayer or PointOnAreaOverlayer for spatial fallback
Output should be feature-level (one feature per address)
final_action and action_reason should be declared as output attributes (varchar) in the relevant transformer
